-- Dana's Largest Shareholder, Schroders, Urges Talks With KNOC, FT Reports
-- Rachel Graham
-- 2010-07-24T08:02:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-24/dana-s-largest-shareholder-schroders-urges-talks-with-knoc-ft-reports.html

          
          
             Dana Petroleum Plc’s  largest
 shareholder , Schroders Plc, is pushing for the U.K. explorer to
negotiate with South Korea’s national oil company on its
takeover offer, the  Financial Times  reported.  
 Schroders has “urged the board to engage at this level,”
 Richard Buxton , head of U.K. equities at the asset manager, was
cited as saying in the report.  Korea National Oil Corp. 
yesterday offered 1,800 pence ($27.77) a share for Dana.  
